{{Quote|Well, R2 units are a dime a dozen.|[[Obi-Wan Kenobi]], on how common R2 units were|<ref name="Downfall of a Droid" />}}
'''R2-series astromech droids''', also known as '''R2 units''', were a very popular series of [[astromech droid]]s produced by [[Industrial Automaton]]. They were the most popular line of all the [[R-series]].<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition">''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''</ref> They stood at around 1 [[meter]] in height, sported a distinctive domed head, and were programmed to perform a variety of tasks. The R2 series was a major success for Industrial Automaton, and many later models of astromech were based on the R2 series, though none had the same success. [[R2-D2]] was a notable example of this model. Although the R2 series was used over a century prior to the [[Clone Wars]], they were still considered to be fairly new during the [[Imperial Era|Age of the Empire]]. According to [[C1-10P]], a [[C1-series astromech droid]], the greatest flaw in R2 units' programming was compassion.<ref name="DiD book">[[Droids in Distress (book)|''Droids in Distress'' chapter book]]</ref>

